The course provides an overview of the classical Mongolian written language as it was used from the 13th century to the mid-20th century (in Mongolia) or to the present day (in the Inner Mongolian Autonomous Region of the People's Republic of China).Objectives/eesmärkid:  Provide an overview of the writing system and orthography of Written Mongolian, the main structures and historical development of the language. Through practical language learning, students will acquire a basic passive knowledge of Mongolian.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Students completing the course will be able to read the Mongolian script, understand simple texts and utterances, and recognise and analyse the main grammatical forms and structures of Written Mongolian. The skills and knowledge acquired during the course will enable the learner to continue learning the language independently.
